      • logHealthCheckIfNeeded

        public static void logHealthCheckIfNeeded(Class<? extends RateProvider> classIdentifier,
                                          String message)
        Logs and checks the frequency of a log info message that is called multiple times in a rate provider, so handles the interval of time of 30 seconds by default to prevent spam.
        Parameters:
        classIdentifier - The class object of the specific rate provider to log.
        message - The message to register in the log.

      • logHealthCheckIfNeeded

        public static void logHealthCheckIfNeeded(Class<? extends RateProvider> classIdentifier,
                                          String message,
                                          long interval)
        Logs and checks the frequency of a log info message that is called multiple times in a rate provider, so handles the interval of time of 30 seconds by default to prevent spam.
        Parameters:
        classIdentifier - The class object of the specific rate provider to log.
        message - The message to register in the log.
        interval - Sets the miliseconds interval of time that a message info log can be reegistered.
